[00:00.49]	[The same. A hall of state: a banquet prepared.,]
[00:01.47]	[Enter SIMONIDES, THAISA, Lords, Attendants, and
[00:01.96]	+ Knights, from tilting]
[00:02.45]SIMONIDES	Knights,
[00:03.60]	To say you're welcome were superfluous.
[00:07.28]	To place upon the volume of your deeds,
[00:10.97]	As in a title-page, your worth in arms,
[00:14.57]	Were more than you expect, or more than's fit,
[00:18.75]	Since every worth in show commends itself.
[00:22.68]	Prepare for mirth, for mirth becomes a feast:
[00:26.77]	You are princes and my guests.
[00:29.72]THAISA	But you, my knight and guest;
[00:32.50]	To whom this wreath of victory I give,
[00:36.11]	And crown you king of this day's happiness.
[00:40.12]PERICLES	'Tis more by fortune, lady, than by merit.
[00:43.80]SIMONIDES	Call it by what you will, the day is yours;
[00:47.73]	And here, I hope, is none that envies it.
[00:51.42]	In framing an artist, art hath thus decreed,
[00:55.43]	To make some good, but others to exceed;
[00:59.12]	And you are her labour'd scholar. Come, queen o'
[01:03.37]	the feast,--
[01:04.68]	For, daughter, so you are,--here take your place:
[01:08.86]	Marshal the rest, as they deserve their grace.
[01:13.04]KNIGHTS	We are honour'd much by good Simonides.
[01:16.72]SIMONIDES	Your presence glads our days: honour we love;
[01:20.82]	For who hates honour hates the gods above.
[01:24.75]Marshal	Sir, yonder is your place.
[01:27.28]PERICLES	Some other is more fit.
[01:29.66]First Knight	Contend not, sir; for we are gentlemen
[01:33.18]	That neither in our hearts nor outward eyes
[01:37.27]	Envy the great nor do the low despise.
[01:40.88]PERICLES	You are right courteous knights.
[01:43.99]SIMONIDES	Sit, sir, sit.
[01:45.46]PERICLES	By Jove, I wonder, that is king of thoughts,
[01:49.39]	These cates resist me, she but thought upon.
[01:53.41]THAISA	By Juno, that is queen of marriage,
[01:56.68]	All viands that I eat do seem unsavoury.
[02:00.45]	Wishing him my meat. Sure, he's a gallant gentleman.
