[02:19.45]PERICLES	Yon king's to me like to my father's picture,
[02:23.62]	Which tells me in that glory once he was;
[02:27.47]	Had princes sit, like stars, about his throne,
[02:31.56]	And he the sun, for them to reverence;
[02:35.09]	None that beheld him, but, like lesser lights,
[02:39.18]	Did vail their crowns to his supremacy:
[02:42.87]	Where now his son's like a glow-worm in the night,
